<div class="min-h-screen bg-gray-50 py-12 px-4">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg p-8">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold display-font mb-2" style="color: #1d3e4c;">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm font-light mb-8" style="color: #657b84;">Last Updated: <%= Date.today.strftime('%B %d, %Y') %></p>

    <div class="space-y-6" style="color: #1d3e4c;">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Introduction</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          HabitBeaver ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our habit tracking application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Information We Collect</h2>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Personal Information</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>Email address (for account creation and login)</li>
          <li>Password (encrypted and securely stored)</li>
          <li>User preferences and settings</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Usage Data</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>Habits you create and track</li>
          <li>Tasks and journals you create</li>
          <li>Completion data and statistics</li>
          <li>Categories and tags you define</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Google Calendar Integration (Optional)</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>Read-only access to your selected Google Calendar</li>
          <li>Calendar event information (title, time, location)</li>
          <li>OAuth refresh token (encrypted and securely stored)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>To provide and maintain the habit tracking service</li>
          <li>To authenticate your account and enable login</li>
          <li>To display your calendar events on your dashboard</li>
          <li>To personalize your experience and remember your preferences</li>
          <li>To improve our application and develop new features</li>
          <li>To send service-related notifications (if enabled)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Storage and Security</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #657b84;">
          We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal information:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>All passwords are encrypted using bcrypt hashing</li>
          <li>OAuth tokens are encrypted before storage</li>
          <li>Data is transmitted over secure HTTPS connections</li>
          <li>Database access is restricted and authenticated</li>
          <li>Regular security updates and patches are applied</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Third-Party Services</h2>

        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Google Calendar API</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #657b84;">
          When you choose to connect your Google Calendar, we use Google's API to access your calendar data. We only request read-only permissions and only access the specific calendar you select. Your calendar data is fetched in real-time and is not permanently stored on our servers.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          Google's use of information received from Google APIs will adhere to the <a href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" class="underline hover:opacity-70">Google API Services User Data Policy</a>, including the Limited Use requirements.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #657b84;">
          We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share your information only in the following circumstances:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li>With your explicit consent</li>
          <li>To comply with legal obligations or valid legal requests</li>
          <li>To protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property</li>
          <li>In connection with a business transfer or acquisition (with notice to you)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Your Rights and Choices</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #657b84;">
          You have the following rights regarding your personal data:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm space-y-1" style="color: #657b84;">
          <li><strong>Access:</strong> You can view all your data within your account settings</li>
          <li><strong>Modification:</strong> You can update your information at any time</li>
          <li><strong>Deletion:</strong> You can delete your account and all associated data</li>
          <li><strong>Export:</strong> You can request a copy of your data</li>
          <li><strong>Disconnect:</strong> You can revoke Google Calendar access at any time</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Cookies and Tracking</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          We use essential cookies to maintain your login session and remember your preferences. We do not use tracking cookies or third-party analytics without your consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          Our service is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected information from a child under 13, please contact us immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #657b84;">
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
          <br><br>
          Email: help@linchpinindustries.com
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t-2" style="border-color: #E8EEF1;">
      <%= link_to root_path, class: "inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-lg text-sm font-semibold transition hover:opacity-90", style: "background-color: #1d3e4c; color: white;" do %>
        <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-left mr-2"></i>Back to Home
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
